flowRoot.flowPara: What is life in San Francisco like. Learn about the technological capital of the US and one of its most interesting cities.

text.tspan: Wikimedia Foundation, San Francisco, CA, USA

flowRoot.flowPara: Graduate of the International Faculty of Engineering at the Technical University of Lodz. While studying he spent two years in Spain, where he participated in the Erasmus programme at the Universidad Politécnica de Valencia.

After graduating, he worked at the University of Virginia in the United States. In November 2012 he moved to San Francisco, California, where he works for the Wikimedia Foundation which is dedicated to the growth and development of Wikipedia and other projects promoting free knowledge.
Challenges you face when when you work on Wikipedia, the 6th most visited website in the world.
What other projects, both related and unrelated to Wikipedia, we tackle.
How Wikimedia Foundation and Wikipedia Community facilitate access to the sum of all human knowledge, also in countries with limited Internet access or ruled by oppressive regimes.
